ENTRY       EC 1.1.1.359                Enzyme
NAME        aldose 1-dehydrogenase [NAD(P)+]
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on the CH-OH group of donors;
            With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
SYSNAME     an aldopyranose:NAD(P)+ 1-oxidoreductase
REACTION    an aldopyranose + NAD(P)+ = an aldono-1,5-lactone + NAD(P)H + H+ [RN:R10428 R10429]
ALL_REAC    R10428 > R08544;
            R10429 > R01096 R07147
SUBSTRATE   aldopyranose [CPD:C20655];
            NAD+ [CPD:C00003];
            NADP+ [CPD:C00006]
PRODUCT     aldono-1,5-lactone [CPD:C20616];
            NADH [CPD:C00004];
            NADPH [CPD:C00005];
            H+ [CPD:C00080]
COMMENT     The enzyme from the archaeon Sulfolobus solfataricus shows broad specificity towards aldoses (D-glucose, D-galactose, D-xylose, L-arabinose, 6-deoxy-D-glucose, D-fucose) and can utilize NAD+ and NADP+ with similar catalytic efficiency. It is involved in aldose catabolism via the branched variant of the Entner-Doudoroff pathway.
